    %h3 1. Information collection &amp; use
    %h4 Website visitors
    %p Like most website operators, NoCoffee SARL collects non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. NoCoffee SARL’s purpose in collecting non-personally identifying information is to better understand how NoCoffee SARL’s visitors use its website. WORDPRESS NoCoffee SARL also collects potentially personally-identifying information like Internet Protocol (IP) addresses. NoCoffee SARL does not use such information to identify its visitors, however, and does not disclose such information.
    %br
    %h4 Newsletter subscribers
    %p You can receive the lastest news and tips on LocomotiveCMS by subscribing to the Newsletter on the website. When you do so, NoCoffee SARL stores your name and email address. You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking on the unsubscribe link at the end of our newsletters.
    %br
    %h4 Demo users
    %p Website visitors who wish to try a demo are asked to provide their name and email address. You will then automatically receive a series of courses on how to use LocomotiveCMS. You will also be registered as Newsletter subscribers. You may opt-out of these communications at any time by clicking on the link at the bottom of our communications to you. Locomotive Editor customers Users who wish to purchase the Locomotive Editor at (lien) are requested to provide the following information : name, email address, billing address and optionally VAT number. We keep this information on file in our secure server. Locomotive Editor customers will then automatically receive a series of courses on how to use LocomotiveCMS and the Locomotive Editor. You will also be registered as Newsletter subscribers. You may opt-out of these communications at any time by clicking on the link at the bottom of our communications to you.
    %br
    %h4 Hosted Solution customers
    %p The LocomotiveCMS Hosted Solution requires a login in order to provide you with a personalized account. During our account registration process, we will collect personally identifiable information (login, name, email address, credit card number, billing address, phone number and op optionally VAT number) and keep this information on file in our secure server in order to process your recurring invoices. This information is only used to verify credit card authenticity, and issue invoices. After completing our registration form, you will receive a welcome email describing your new LocomotiveCMS account, and how to access that account Upon discontinuation of LocomotiveCMS Hosted Solution, your information will be destroyed on our billing system. If we are unable to process your subscription for a given month, this information, along with your account information, may be used to contact you.
    %br
    %br
    %h3 2. Communications from NoCoffee SARL
    %h4 Service-related Announcements
    %p We will send you service-related announcements on rare occasions when it is necessary to do so. For instance, if our service is temporarily suspended for maintenance, we might send you an email. Generally, you may not opt-out of these communications, which are not promotional in nature. If you do not wish to receive them, you have the option to deactivate your account.
    %br
    %h4 Other Messages
    %p We may also send you messages from time to time about new features or services that we will offer to our users. You may opt-out of these communications at any time by clicking on the link at the bottom of our communications to you.
    %br
    %h4 Customer Service
    %p Upon issuing a customer support request to NoCoffee SARL / LocomotiveCMS, we may use your information and email address to contact you regarding your inquiry.
    %br
    %br
    %h3 3. Privacy Policy Changes
    %p Although most changes are likely to be minor, NoCoffee SARL may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in its sole discretion. NoCoffee SARL encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.
    %br
    %br
    %h3 4. Questions or Concerns
    %p If you have any questions or concerns regarding our privacy policies, please send us a detailed message at contact@locomotivecms.com. We will make every effort to resolve your concerns.
